  "prompt": "Which are the best productivity techniques to get things done?",
  "response": "Here are some of the best productivity techniques:\n\n1. Pomodoro Technique\n- Work in 25-minute focused intervals\n- Take short breaks between sessions\n- Helps maintain concentration and prevent burnout\n\n2. Time Blocking\n- Schedule specific time slots for tasks\n- Reduces decision fatigue\n- Improves time management\n\n3. GTD (Getting Things Done)\n- Capture all tasks in a system\n- Break tasks into actionable steps\n- Regularly review and organize tasks\n\n4. Eisenhower Matrix\n- Prioritize tasks based on urgency and importance\n- Helps focus on high-impact activities\n- Reduces time spent on low-value tasks\n\n5. Two-Minute Rule\n- If a task takes less than two minutes, do it immediately\n- Prevents small tasks from accumulating\n- Builds momentum\n\n6. Deep Work\n- Dedicate uninterrupted time to complex tasks\n- Minimize distractions\n- Enhance focus and quality of work\n\n7. SMART Goals\n- Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound\n- Provides clear direction\n- Makes goals more actionable\n\n8. Eat That Frog\n- Complete most challenging task first\n- Builds motivation\n- Reduces procrastination\n\nEach technique suits different work styles, so experiment to find what works best for you.",
